{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fullscreen","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Full screen window covers the entire display area of a screen and has no decorations. The display’s video mode is not changed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" Multi-window full-screen mode has a 1px border of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/environment\/defaults\/defaultClearColor"},{"text":" color.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On macOS:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" A new desktop is used to display the running project.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Regardless of the platform, enabling full screen will change the window size to match the monitor’s size. Therefore, make sure your project supports "},{"type":"text","text":"multiple resolutions"},{"text":" when enabling full screen mode.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Full screen mode with full multi-window support."}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DisplayServer","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DisplayServer\/WindowMode"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/displayserver\/windowmode\/fullscreen"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DisplayServer\/WindowMode\/fullscreen","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"m